column2: Ice off two weeks ago- beautiful weather- with slight breeze
Very windy- clear day- rain yesterday.  Lake level: very high
Assume noon for the time. Assume that temperature and dissolved oxygen profile was taken at the deep hole.
Breezy and fair amount of cloud cover- not ideal conditions for secchi but training session with Sandy Wickman. Participants were Rick Green- Rick Wollerman- Bill Cerny- Gary Gruca- and Fritz Behr.
Cloudless- beautiful- crisp day- ideal for secchi reading.  Assisted by Margaret Behr.  Spotted two immature loons and adult eagle in new nest.
Eagles have built a new nest on "Virgin Island" since last Fall and were observed on the nest.  Also observed one loon pair. Data collected by Gary Gruca and Fritz Behr
Observed loon and eagle on nest.
Satellite day.  Observed loon and eagle on nest.  Perfect day for secchi.
Loon chick is MIA- baby eagle sticking head above nest- smallmouth bass on nests. Good day for secchi.   Assisted by Margaret Behr
Data collected by Bill Cerny and Gary Gruca
Wind made it hard to stay anchored over 48' hole
Satellite day.  Data collected by Rick Wollerman
Data collected by Gary Gruca and Bill Cerny.  Perfect day for secchi reading.
Satellite day.  Sechhi reading by Bill Cerny.

Collected water sample to be analyzed for lead- mercury- conductivity- alkalinity- hardness- and pH. Sample collection assisted by Gary Gruca. Results - conductivity: 24.2 uS/cm- pH: 6.92- alkalinity: 6.52 mg/L- calcium: 15.9 mg/L- magnesium: 5.86 mg/L- hardness: 63.9 mg/L- lead: ND- mercury: ND.
